## ğŸ“Š What Gets Documented?

The generator automatically extracts:

### From Views/ViewSets:
- âœ… URL paths and patterns
- âœ… HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
- âœ… View docstrings as descriptions
- âœ… Authentication classes
- âœ… Permission classes

### From Serializers:
- âœ… Field names and types
- âœ… Required/optional status
- âœ… Read-only/write-only fields
- âœ… Field help text
- âœ… Choices/enums
- âœ… Validation constraints (max_length, min_value, etc.)
- âœ… Nested serializers

### From Filter Backends:
- âœ… Filterable fields
- âœ… Search fields
- âœ… Ordering fields
- âœ… Pagination parameters

---

## ğŸ“„ Output Formats

### PDF
Professional documentation with:
- Cover page with title, version, and generation date
- Table of contents
- Detailed endpoint documentation
- Request/response examples
- Field tables with types and constraints

### HTML
Interactive documentation with:
- Dark theme UI
- Sidebar navigation
- Syntax-highlighted JSON examples
- Method badges (GET=green, POST=blue, etc.)
- Responsive design

### JSON (OpenAPI 3.0)
Standard specification compatible with:
- Swagger UI
- Postman
- Redoc
- OpenAPI Generator
- Any OpenAPI-compatible tool

